International Pride Month #Day18

@haus.of.rage brings you the best night of all nights. It was a Grand Success with all you beautiful people on the floor. People from the community and their amazing allies. 🏳️‍🌈 

Thank you everyone for coming together every time. We love you from all our hearts 

Bringing you live from @kittysuindia @thelalitmumbai

@sushantdivgikr you’re the best..!! 
The love we have for you is beyond anything. 😘😘😘🏳️‍🌈❤️🏳️‍🌈❤️

The last number was such an impromptu one and so damn good. It shows how the connect you create and maintain shows in the collective projects you do.

Thank you @prashantchauhan689 @dancing_queens_lgbtq @princess_queen_urmi @abhijitrthakur3699 @gentleman_gaga @naazbee_ @rachel_anthony_lewis @mayurparmar215 for bringing in your kick ass fabulousness. It wouldn’t have been complete without you.

This International Pride month, let's "Find Pride" 🏳️‍🌈 

Find pride within ourselves. 
Let's help find Pride within others. 
Let us all come together for a cause and 
This time once again not limit it to these 30 days. 
Let's spread awareness the way we spread joy. 

I urge you all to come out and share your stories - your beautiful, inspiring and emotional stories. It is your experience that you share could help shape someone's future. We have that kind of responsibility bestowed upon us because it is the stories that we hear shapes the person that we become. 

I started following this campaign of #30DaysofPride in Year 2020. Since then I have had the chance to interact with all you amazing 30,000 people and more who have been diligently following Inder and me. I request you all to share your stories starting today. Try it out once and see the power of the Rainbow yourselves. 

Sharing my short story of Finding Pride with Google.

Share yours with #30DaysOfPride 🌈

Its FINALLY Out 🤩

A feature we did with @google produced
by @viceasia 

For the LGTBQIA+ community, the discovery and acceptance of identity is complex and unique. It's also filled
with joy. 

Four members of the community in Asia Pacific share some of the questions they asked, and the queer spaces and
businesses they uncovered, that helped them celebrate who they are, no matter who they love or how they identify.

See our stories of chaos-free travel, finding the perfect fit, discovering an accepting community and the power of
feeling comfortable in your body. Link in Bio

latestPosts.caption:
🌈 Celebrating Love Unbound 🌟

In a world where traditions meet the winds of change, love knows no boundaries. 🏳️‍🌈 This Karwachauth, we rewrite the rituals, not just with ink but with our hearts. 📜💖

In a land where love was once confined to conventions, we dare to dream beyond those lines. 🌄✨

🌸🌼🌸 A New Chapter of Love 🌸🌼🌸

In the embrace of the timeless moon, two souls unite, transcending the barriers of societal norms. 🌕👭

We light the diya of acceptance and stand as a beacon for love, no matter the gender. 🕯️🏳️‍🌈

Our hearts beat in rhythm with the thali’s melody, celebrating love’s eternal bond. 🥁💞

Together, we break the fast, not just of hunger, but of prejudices, one morsel at a time. 🍽️🤝

So, let the channi of tradition sift through our love, leaving only the pure essence of acceptance behind. 🌾❤️

This Karwachauth, we redefine love, and our love story is written with the ink of courage and the parchment of hope. 🖋️📜

Love is love, and together we are redefining traditions, one step at a time. 🏳️‍🌈💪🌟

#LoveUnbound #KarwachauthWithPride #redefiningtraditions

latestPosts.caption:
Let me tell you something, baby queer — they’re gonna throw words at you. Meetha. Soft. Sweet. Too much. Too little. Too loud. Too proud. And guess what? That’s exactly how you know you’re doing it right.

They painted it on a wall thinking it would sting — like the word meetha was supposed to shrink me. Joke’s on them. I turned it into my backdrop. Aesthetic, isn’t it?

You see, when they can’t box you in, they label you. When they can’t dim your light, they call it ‘too bright.’ And when you dare to live out loud, they scramble for slurs hoping you’ll sit down and shrink. But you? You better pose.

Unapologetic. Unfiltered. Unfazed.

Because what they meant as a slur, I now wear like glitter on my collarbone.

So to the younger ones watching — let them talk. You weren’t made for their comfort. You were made to be seen, heard, and worshipped in your full technicolor glory.

Strike a pose, darling. Because meetha never looked this powerful

#MeethaAndMajestic #SlurToScenery #QueerAndUnbothered #UnfilteredUnfazedUnapologetic #OwnYourSweetness #QueerIndia #BoldAndBeautiful #ReclaimItAll #SweetWithSpice #LoudProudAndStillTooMuch
